eutp a subdomain for owncloud, nothing else will be at that subdomain. i would hate to have to go to cloud.mydomain.com/owncloud/. it's redundant feeling.\r\n\r\nsimply going to cloud.mydomain.com would be much preferred.\r\n\r\ni've been building web software for a long time. in every project i've ever worked on i always strive to think of all the possible use-cases and to build for those use-cases. i realize you can't catch all possible use-cases, but installing to the root of a website is probably a pretty popular use-case. therefore, you should allow people to install where they like, not where you think they should be installing.\r\n\r\ninstalling to ./ or to / results in errors. easiest way that i've found to get owncloud in your root is to just install to the owncloud folder, then after it's installed, move all the files and folders in the owncloud folder to the root of your site."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/19573037","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/2626#issuecomment-19573037","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/2626","id":19573037,"user":{"login":"mredofcourse","id":4722057,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/86dc279daf55907a89fd81b542861fb0?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fc4d3364765df700b586eb6003da6b5dc.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"86dc279daf55907a89fd81b542861fb0","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mredofcourse","html_url":"https://github.com/mredofcourse","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mredofcourse/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mredofcourse/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mredofcourse/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mredofcourse/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mredofcourse/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mredofcourse/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mredofcourse/repo